<TITLE> Police nab Bangla Bhai aide </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, Apr 24 (bdnews24.com)  Police has arrested an associate of Siddiqul Islam, alias Bangla Bhai, leader of the banned Islamist out Jamaat-ul-Mujahideen Bangladesh (JMB) from Naogaon. The arrested, one hafez Masud, operation officer of JMB, was held from Maskipur Bazar of Atrai Upazila early on Saturday. He is the son of Taslim Uddin of Patisar village under the same upazila. Atrai police chief Moazzem Hossain told bdnews24.com that Masud was absconding in many cases, including four murders, abduction, loot and extortion. He was also a top JMB member. The official sad Masud, led by Shayekh Abdur Rahman and Bangla Bhai, killed and kidnapped men and collected ransom at Atrai and Raninagar Upazilas in Noagaon in 2004. On Apr 24, 2004, Masud and his assistants killed a retired soldier Sheikh Farid at Mirza High School premises in the presence of Bangla Bhai. The deceased was killed for his involvement with Sharbahara, another banned ultra leftist organisation. The JMB member was missing since the arrest of Bangla Bhai. He was allegedly trying to gather JMB members in the locality. bdnews24.
